What zones mobs do not like illusions?<br>
What mobs do not like illusions?<br>
<br>
I looked around to try to find another post that had information, but could not find one.  I know that in Shadow Haven for example I was going to use my water elemental form for the water breathing  so I would not need fishscale, but found out abrubtly that they do not like my illusion.<br>
<br>
Are there more places to watch out for?<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
Mett 34 DE enchanter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=charmroxors>Charmroxors</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#330000>(4/3/03 1:11:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=264.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question:  Where not to use illusion?</span><hr size=1> in general a lot of mobs and npc's dont like the elemental illusions, but there are also cases where you will have to use the elemental illusions to interact with some npc's (i.e. the brownies in lesser faydark). the only illusions you wouldnt want to use are ones that you know will put you KoS with the npc's/mobs you're dealing with. i like troll illusion, cant beat that extra tick of regen stacked with regen3 =) .. but my favorite is iksar illusion... iksars look so badass wearing a bright green or white robe. =)<br>
<br>
 <p>Charmroxors<br>
60chanter<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=555166" target="_new">my gear</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=astyd>astyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#330000>(4/4/03 9:54:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=264.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question:  Where not to use illusion?</span><hr size=1> <br>
Non-Humanish illusions are KoS just about everywhere.  Evil Races are generally KoS in Good Cities and vice versa.  Wolf Form is KoS in many places.  Gorenaire is KoS to illusions.<br>
<br>
Pretty much Illusions are good away from Guards.  Batwings and Fish Scales are sold in EC by the Erudite with Spell Components.  I know they are for sale in other places as well.<br>
<br>
Cames Houdini<br>
Level 63 Chanter - Vazelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shyanha>Shyanha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(4/10/03 7:46:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=264.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question:  Where not to use illusion?</span><hr size=1> When you head to DL make sure you find out whether Gore is on track or not.  I'm not sure of her respawn time.  I've had answers from 3 days to 2 weeks given to me!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Anyway, she hates illusions, from what I've been told, and Any illusion will make you KoS to her. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bregaladlow>Bregalad LoW</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#330000>(4/30/03 3:00:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=264.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question:  Where not to use illusion?</span><hr size=1> Well, actually a recent patch fixed this.  I did not do extensive testing, but I know that Imp Illusion I use to levitate was previously KoS in Vah Shir outpost in Grimling and to Coldain in GD.   After patch, they don't mind my imp form any more. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bregalad Alcarin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, High Elf Phantasmist, Xev &lt;Legends of Westwood&gt;<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.webspan.net/~scorpio/graph/mezzed.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sildiil>Sildiil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#330000>(5/1/03 11:11:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=264.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question:  Where not to use illusion?</span><hr size=1> As I understood the recent patch change on illusions, They still let you fool guards and such with the racial illusions, but spirit wolf, elementals, skellies and such have no effect on factions with NPC's or Mobs.  Seems dumb to me that I can put on the smurf suit and fool a wiz in third gate, but a 1st level skellie will immediately see me for the lilly skinned high elf that I am when I'm dressed for halloween. I am sure glad I have all the bottled mana spells since the brownies can't be fooled, at least not by our illusions. I understand that wolf form cast by a druid will still let you trade with the brownies. WE are supposed to be the masters of illusion and this change bites.<br>
<br>
Silvisage 50 enchanter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wikkin23>Wikkin23</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.wikkin.com/lilpic.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#330000>(5/2/03 9:11:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=264.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://wikkin.com/pic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question:  Where not to use illusion?</span><hr size=1> If you change your race to a race that can not be a player-character, you are treated now by ALL NPC's as if you were your default race.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Eample</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: I am a Gnomish enchanter. In Werewolf form, ALL NPC's now treat me the same as if I were a Gnome.<br>
<br>
This does not seem to be the case for druids, however. Their wolf form seems to still get them killed in places like PoJ. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=181046&resize=true" target=_new><img src="http://www.wikkin.com/wikkin_sig.jpg" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showPrevMessage?topicID=264.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showNextMessage?topicID=264.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=264.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.threadControl?topicID=264.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=264.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=264.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub136.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="eqenchantersrealmfrm11">General<option value="eqenchantersrealmadminnotices">Admin Notices<option value="eqenchantersrealmfrm12">Equipment<option value="eqenchantersrealmspells">Sp